Basically, a partition algorithm, instead of blindly thinking of sorthing, when speration or partition or region kinda problem comes up think about this THREE POINTERS algorithm. Basically 3 regions (mid part automatically handled)

Concept is: 
-> 0  to low as one region
-> low to mid as one region
-> mid to high as one region, 
and you gonna scan with the mid pointer keeping all the array elements as unknown to put the current elemen in the proper region.

Keynote to mind:
1. When u put the low value and move the pointer u need to move mid, cause technically the 0 to low to mid region is already sorted and obviously mid here is working as a pointer. 
2. And when u push high regoin value that is swap with mid, u are not moving mid here cause it's a new value now you got with the position of high pointer. 
